<Docs title="Observer" description="MobX reactions + typed event emitters." eyebrow="Pattern">
  <p>
    <strong>Where:</strong> MobX <code>autorun</code>/<code>reaction</code> for continuous state;
    <code>pixi-reels</code>' <code>EventEmitter&lt;ReelSetEvents&gt;</code> for discrete domain events.
  </p>
  <p><strong>The rule:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Continuous state → MobX reaction.</li>
    <li>Discrete event ("reel landed") → event emitter.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Both are observer patterns; pick the primitive that fits the shape of the data.
    Reactions that fire every frame while reels spin are the wrong shape for "reel landed."
  </p>
</Docs>
